quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  41,1,Ha Mim
  41,2,"A revelation from the Beneficent, the Merciful"
  41,3,"A Book (Scripture) whereof the verses are expounded, an Arabic Quran (Lecture) for a people who understand"
  41,4,"Giving good news and a warning, but most of them turn aside so they hear not"
  41,5,"And they say, \"Our heart are under veils from that to which you call us, and there is a deafness in our ears, and a screen hangs between us and you. So do you (as you will), we too are doing (what we will)"
  41,6,"Say (O Muhammad), \"I am only a mortal like you; it is revealed to me that your God is one Allah, therefore follow the right way to Him and ask His forgiveness\". And woe unto the idolaters (those who join gods with Allah)"
  41,7,Those who give not regular charity and who deny the Hereafter
  41,8,"Those who believe and do good, they shall surely have a reward unfailing"
  41,9,"Say, \"What! Do you indeed disbelieve in Him Who created the earth in two Days (periods), and do you set up rivals with Him? He (none else) is the Lord of the Worlds"
  41,10,"And He made in it firm mountains rising above its surface, and He blessed the earth and measured therein the sustenance for all things in four Days (periods), alike (or in accordance with their needs) for all seekers"
  41,11,"He directed Himself to the heaven when it was smoke (or gas), so He said unto it and unto the earth, \"Come you together (or both), willingly or unwillingly.\" They both said, \" We come in willing obedience"